[1] Feline, human - Pennsylvania
Date: 11 Aug 2010
Source: Reading Eagle [edited]
<http://readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=240785>


A feral kitten found in Spring Township last week has tested positive
for rabies, and one person who was scratched by it has been treated,
according to Pennsylvania Department of Health.

The person treated after being scratched lived in the neighborhood.
No further information was available about that person.

The kitten was acting strangely, prompting someone in the
neighborhood to take it to a veterinarian's office Wednesday or
Thursday, department press secretary Holli E. Senior said. The kitten
was euthanized at the office and tested positive for rabies in a
state lab on Thursday [5 Aug 2010?]. The kitten was part of a litter
of feral kittens that lived in the Chapel Hill Road area, Senior said.

--
